REFLECTION API
 To inspect or modify the classes, interfaces, fields and methods at runtime, without knowing the names of the classes, methods etc
 It can manipulate private members of the class too.
 Reflection API is used in frameworks like Spring, Hibernate (where objects are created sung Reflection)

1. Using Reflection, we can create object without using new keyword

Create obejct using Class.newInstance()
Create obejct using Constructor.newInstance()

2. Using Reflection, the private methods can be invoked


difference Between Class.newInstance() and Constructor.newInstance()

Class.newInstance()                                              Constructor.newInstance()
1. invokes only default constructor                             1. Invokes any type of constructor,
2. invokes only the defined or visisble constuctor              2. invokes default constructor or no-arg constructor
3. throws all exceptions thrown by the constructor              3. Wraps all exceptions thrown by the constructor as InvokationTargetException
